# Cloud Monitoring and Alerting Using AWS CloudWatch

## Description
This project demonstrates real-time cloud monitoring and alerting using AWS CloudWatch. An EC2 instance is monitored for CPU utilization, and automated email alerts are triggered via Amazon SNS when CPU usage exceeds a defined threshold.

---

## Architecture
- An Amazon EC2 instance generates performance metrics
- Amazon CloudWatch monitors CPU utilization
- A CloudWatch alarm evaluates the metric against a threshold
- Amazon SNS sends email notifications when the alarm is triggered

---

## AWS Services Used
- Amazon EC2
- Amazon CloudWatch
- Amazon SNS

---

## Monitoring and Alert Configuration
- **Metric:** CPUUtilization  
- **Statistic:** Average  
- **Threshold:** ≥ 35%  
- **Period:** 1 minute  
- **Evaluation Periods:** 2 out of 2  
- **Notification:** SNS Email  

---

## Testing and Validation
- CPU load was generated on the EC2 instance using Linux commands
- CPU utilization crossed the defined threshold
- CloudWatch alarm transitioned from OK to ALARM state
- Email notification was successfully received via SNS
- After stopping the load, the alarm returned to OK state

